natfree (1.6) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Change default IP number to 15th
  * Added hooks for pre-up, post-up, pre-down, post-down, pre-create
    and post-create in natfree-iface.
  * Binary package natfree-server has been removed and replaced by:
    natfree-flat-server (uses default configuration to set IP address
    to natfree interface on start) and natfree-flex-server (no IP
    configuration by default). The intended use for flat-server is a computer
    lab with a dedicate VLAN whereas flex-server would be used in regular
    classroom to temporary comunication with a portable laptops trolley.
  * In a similar manner, natfree-client has been splited into
    natfree-flat-client, for(computer lab clients, searching for server in the
    same lan, and  natfree-flex-client for use in portable laptops trolleys,
    the default flex configuration uses DHCP option 126 to get the server
    network address/mask. 
    configuration by default). The intended use for flat-server is a computer
    lab with a dedicate VLAN whereas flex-server would be used in regular
    classroom to temporary comunication with laptops or a set of computers in
    a different network.
  * Added hook scripts in server packages to configure DNS resolution using
    update-hosts tool.

 -- Luis Garcia Gisbert <luisgg@gmail.com>  Tue, 04 Feb 2025 12:45:35 +0100

